## Walkthrough the stock balance report in the erpnext project ##
### Link to stock balance module https://github.com/frappe/erpnext/blob/develop/erpnext/stock/report/stock_balance

To start with, stock balance simply calculates the total balance quantity of items for each items in the inventory with the current warehouse information,

With the use of filters it filters out the stock movements to different warehouse within that time frame.

The in and out qty defines the total quantity of an item that is moved through the stocks by purchasing of that items or
by selling them out of the stocks.

These values are calculated through stock ledger entry which are a subtable for stock entry which is used to store movements of stock through the ERP.